    <description>
Noel is a part-time professor at Inter-American University in the
southern Puerto Rican town of Ponce.  He recalls Hurricane Georges
that hit Puerto Rico in 1998 and left his family without electricity
and power for over a month and a half.  However, the experience with
Hurricane Maria in his central town of Utuado was twice as bad,
leaving his town without basic utilities for 5 months.  His family and
friends are still coping with the psychological trauma.
